04:05.171 --> 04:08.208
CAPTIONS PAID FOR BY
DISCOVERY COMMUNICATIONS

04:13.479 --> 04:14.915
[ SCOFFS ]

04:14.915 --> 04:18.084
I SEE YOUR TRIPS TO PARIS,
TO ASPEN, THE MONEY.

04:18.084 --> 04:20.286
GOD KNOWS YOU SPEND MONEY.

04:20.286 --> 04:22.556
WHAT DO I ASK OF YOU?

04:22.556 --> 04:23.757
NOTHING.

04:23.757 --> 04:29.489
ALL I WANT IS FOR YOU
TO TREAT ME AND MY SON FAIRLY.

04:30.163 --> 04:32.866
AND YOU DARE INSULT ME
AND MAKE THIS ABOUT MONEY?!

04:32.866 --> 04:34.200
YOU'RE STANDING IN MY OFFICE,

04:34.200 --> 04:35.869
YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT TRIPS
TO ASPEN, TRIPS TO PARIS,

04:35.869 --> 04:37.604
YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT MY HOUSE,
ABOUT MY STUFF.

04:37.604 --> 04:40.006
YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT
ALL THE THINGS I HAVE
THAT YOU DON'T HAVE,

04:40.006 --> 04:41.407
AND THEN YOU HAVE THE NERVE

04:41.407 --> 04:43.810
TO TELL ME THAT
YOU'RE NOT TALKING ABOUT MONEY?

04:43.810 --> 04:45.345
OF COURSE YOU ARE,
CELINE.

04:45.345 --> 04:47.514
IT'S ALWAYS ABOUT MONEY.

04:47.514 --> 04:50.617
GO TO HELL!

04:50.617 --> 04:54.655
IT'S NOT ABOUT THE MONEY,
YOU STUPID MAN.

04:56.990 --> 04:59.626
IT'S NEVER BEEN ABOUT
THE MONEY.

05:01.968 --> 05:04.137
GOD, I HATE SEEING YOU
EVERY DAY.

05:04.137 --> 05:06.339
THEN LEAVE!

05:06.339 --> 05:10.343
THAT WOULD BE TOO EASY.

05:10.343 --> 05:15.081
AND LET ME REMIND YOU
ABOUT SOMETHING, MR. JIM CRYER.

05:15.081 --> 05:17.183
I KNOW EVERYTHING.

05:17.183 --> 05:18.752
<i>EVERYTHING.</i>

05:18.752 --> 05:20.721
DON'T PUSH ME.

05:20.721 --> 05:23.189
GOD, DON'T PUSH ME.

05:32.899 --> 05:35.268
[ SIGHS ]

05:37.904 --> 05:40.807
YOU'RE STILL HERE?

05:40.807 --> 05:43.644
FINE. I'LL LEAVE AS SOON
AS I CAN GET AWAY FROM BENNY.

05:45.612 --> 05:47.614
WHERE IS HE?

05:47.614 --> 05:49.415
IN THE BATHROOM.

06:14.180 --> 06:18.418
CANDACE, THAT BOY DIDN'T KILL
THAT BABY.

06:22.222 --> 06:23.924
BELIEVE WHAT YOU WANT.

06:23.924 --> 06:26.860
I WILL.

06:26.860 --> 06:31.197
I FEEL IT IN MY SPIRIT.

06:33.366 --> 06:37.470
HE MAY BE A THUG
AND A HUSTLER AND A LIAR.

06:37.470 --> 06:40.340
Y'ALL HAVE THAT
IN COMMON.

06:40.340 --> 06:42.643
YOU MANIPULATE PEOPLE

06:42.643 --> 06:45.345
AND USE THEM
TO DO WHATEVER YOU WANT.

06:45.345 --> 06:49.015
I BELIEVE THAT BOY HUSTLED YOU
OUT OF THAT $50,000,

06:49.015 --> 06:52.385
AND HE USED YOUR SON...

06:52.385 --> 06:54.888
TO DO IT
AS HIS TRUMP CARD.

06:57.658 --> 07:00.193
BUT I DON'T BELIEVE HE KILLED
THAT BABY.

07:00.193 --> 07:05.105
YOU SEE HOW THIS JUST GOES
AROUND AND AROUND IN A CIRCLE?

07:05.105 --> 07:07.340
YOU DO IT TO SOMEBODY,
THEY DO IT TO YOU.

07:07.340 --> 07:10.343
DO YOU SEE THAT,
DAUGHTER?

07:10.343 --> 07:12.012
THEN WHERE IS HE?

07:12.012 --> 07:14.681
I DON'T KNOW.

07:14.681 --> 07:17.450
BUT I'M GONNA FIND HIM.

07:22.923 --> 07:25.291
DON'T YOU HAVE A BIBLE
TO READ?

07:25.291 --> 07:29.796
WE CAN START IN GENESIS,
EXODUS,

07:29.796 --> 07:33.033
LEVITICUS, NUMBERS,

07:33.033 --> 07:39.305
NEHEMIAH, JOB,
PSALMS, REVELATIONS.

07:39.305 --> 07:42.275
YOU NEED THEM ALL, BABY.

07:49.382 --> 07:51.084
SO, DO YOU LIKE IT?

07:51.084 --> 07:53.486
I THINK YOU'LL LOOK
REALLY HANDSOME.

07:53.486 --> 07:55.722
THANK YOU.

07:55.722 --> 07:59.325
AND, UH, YOUR WIFE WILL BE THERE
TOMORROW?

07:59.325 --> 08:01.502
YES.
GOOD.

08:01.502 --> 08:03.504
[ KNOCK ON DOOR, DOOR OPENS ]

08:03.504 --> 08:05.238
MAGGIE,
WHAT IS THE WHOLE POLICY

08:05.238 --> 08:06.573
ON THE HIRING AND FIRING
OF INTERNS AROUND HERE?

08:06.573 --> 08:08.208
EXCUSE ME?

08:08.208 --> 08:11.377
CARLOS, THE INTERN ‐‐
FIRE HIM.

08:11.377 --> 08:12.713
WHY? WHAT DID HE DO?

08:12.713 --> 08:14.447
FIRE HIM.

08:14.447 --> 08:17.283
OKAY.
THANK YOU.

08:17.283 --> 08:19.419
IS EVERYTHING ALL RIGHT?

08:19.419 --> 08:23.323
YES, EVERYTHING IS ‐‐
EVERYTHING IS FINE.

08:23.323 --> 08:25.025
IT'S FINE.

08:25.025 --> 08:26.159
MM.

08:26.159 --> 08:27.694
OKAY, WELL,
I WAS JUST TALKING TO DAVID

08:27.694 --> 08:29.663
ABOUT THE ANNOUNCEMENT
TOMORROW.

08:29.663 --> 08:32.265
WE HAVE COVERAGE
FROM EVERY NATIONAL NEWSPAPER,

08:32.265 --> 08:33.433
AND THERE'S EVEN TALK OF

08:33.433 --> 08:35.235
A SPECIAL BROADCAST LIVE
FROM THE ANNOUNCEMENT.

08:35.235 --> 08:37.070
GOOD.

08:37.070 --> 08:40.607
YEAH. REALLY, JIM, COME ON.
DON'T SOUND SO EXCITED.

08:40.607 --> 08:41.842
COME ON. HE IS.

08:41.842 --> 08:45.145
IT'S JUST...BEEN A VERY TRYING
TIME WITH WYATT.

08:45.145 --> 08:46.780
NO, I‐I KNOW.

08:46.780 --> 08:48.582
I MEAN, GOD, I'M GLAD
THEY CAUGHT THE REAL GUY, BUT...

08:48.582 --> 08:50.250
MM.
[CHUCKLES]

08:50.250 --> 08:52.686
...YOU'VE GOT TO ADMIT, THIS HAS
BEEN TREMENDOUSLY HELPFUL

08:52.686 --> 08:54.555
FOR THE CAMPAIGN ‐‐
LOTS OF MEDIA EXPOSURE.

08:54.555 --> 08:57.323
YEAH.
THAT'S GREAT.

08:57.323 --> 08:59.092
LISTEN,
TOMORROW'S A HUGE DAY,

08:59.092 --> 09:01.067
SO LET'S GO OVER YOUR SPEECH
AND RUNDOWN AGAIN.

09:01.067 --> 09:01.968
OKAY.

09:01.968 --> 09:03.637
NOW, I THINK ‐‐
VERONICA.

09:08.274 --> 09:11.044
HELLO, JIM.

09:11.044 --> 09:12.646
HELLO, VERONICA.

09:12.646 --> 09:16.517
YOU LOOK LOVELY TODAY.

09:16.517 --> 09:19.019
DAVID,
I NEED TO SPEAK WITH YOU.

09:19.019 --> 09:21.655
SURE.

09:21.655 --> 09:23.657
HERE.
DON'T FORGET YOUR TIE.

09:23.657 --> 09:25.158
YOU'LL LOOK GREAT.

09:25.158 --> 09:28.729
MAYBE YOU CAN WEAR SOMETHING
TO COORDINATE WITH HIM.

09:31.397 --> 09:36.803
YOU KNOW, YOU REALLY DO PAY
CLOSE ATTENTION TO MY HUSBAND.

09:36.803 --> 09:38.739
[ SCOFFS ]

09:38.739 --> 09:40.807
LOOK,
I'M JUST DOING MY JOB.

09:40.807 --> 09:43.476
DO IT OVER HERE.

09:46.446 --> 09:49.616
YOU KNOW, YOU'RE NOT
THE FIRST POSSESSIVE
WIFE I'VE ENCOUNTERED.

09:52.018 --> 09:54.320
EXCUSE ME.

09:58.725 --> 10:01.502
BUT I WILL BE THE LAST.

10:05.171 --> 10:08.842
DO IT OVER THERE.
HE'S BETTER GAME.

10:08.842 --> 10:10.877
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

10:10.877 --> 10:13.279
CAN MY WIFE AND I HAVE
A MOMENT ALONE, PLEASE?

10:13.279 --> 10:15.516
SURE, SURE, SURE.

10:15.516 --> 10:18.785
DID IT JUST GET REALLY COLD
IN HERE?

10:18.785 --> 10:22.055
COME ON.
[ CHUCKLES ]

10:29.630 --> 10:31.632
[ SIGHS ]

10:34.200 --> 10:36.136
REALLY, DAVID?

10:39.339 --> 10:42.743
YOU BRING OUR SON
TO THAT HOTEL,

10:42.743 --> 10:48.803
YOU LET HIM HANG OUT
WITH THAT FLAMING...HOMOSEXUAL,

10:49.149 --> 10:52.185
AND YOU CHEAT ON ME
WITH HER?

10:52.185 --> 10:53.720
NO, NO.
WAIT, WAIT, WAIT.

10:53.720 --> 10:55.822
I DON'T KNOW WHO'S SLEEPING
WITH WHO.

10:55.822 --> 10:58.792
NOW HOLD ON BEFORE
YOU SAY SOMETHING YOU'LL REGRET.

10:58.792 --> 11:02.035
I WON'T REGRET
ANYTHING I SAY.

11:02.035 --> 11:05.772
NOW, VERONICA,
YOU KNOW ME.

11:07.974 --> 11:10.644
I THOUGHT I DID.

11:10.644 --> 11:13.013
I DID NOT SLEEP WITH HER.

11:13.013 --> 11:14.548
I DON'T BELIEVE YOU.

11:14.548 --> 11:15.749
YOU SAYING I'M A LIAR?

11:15.749 --> 11:19.185
OH, WE ESTABLISHED THAT ALREADY,
HONEY,

11:19.185 --> 11:22.889
WHEN YOU LIED
ABOUT JIM AND BENJAMIN YOUNG.

11:22.889 --> 11:25.391
[ SIGHS ]

11:25.391 --> 11:28.228
WHY DID YOU COME HERE?

11:28.228 --> 11:31.598
KATHERYN IS HAVING
A DINNER PARTY TONIGHT

11:31.598 --> 11:34.768
TO CELEBRATE
THIS HUGE ANNOUNCEMENT.

11:34.768 --> 11:37.270
I EXPECT YOU
TO BE THERE.

11:37.270 --> 11:40.907
YES, I WILL BE THERE.

11:40.907 --> 11:43.076
COULD HAVE CALLED
AND TOLD ME THAT ON THE PHONE.

11:43.076 --> 11:45.245
NO.

11:45.245 --> 11:47.147
YOU NEVER ANNOUNCE
YOUR PRESENCE

11:47.147 --> 11:49.583
WHEN THERE'S A SEDUCING WHORE
ON THE LOOSE.

11:52.285 --> 11:53.520
[ CHUCKLES ]

11:53.520 --> 11:55.722
YOU SURPRISE HER
AT EVERY TURN.

11:58.124 --> 12:00.567
ARE YOU GONNA GIVE ME
JEFFERY'S CAR?

12:00.567 --> 12:03.203
NO.

12:03.203 --> 12:05.906
I CAME HERE
TO SPEAK MY PEACE.

12:05.906 --> 12:11.612
NOW, I WILL STAND WITH YOU
AT YOUR BIG ANNOUNCEMENT,

12:11.612 --> 12:15.181
BUT YOU ARE NOT
TO COME HOME.

12:15.181 --> 12:18.118
IS THAT CLEAR, DAVID?

12:20.654 --> 12:23.056
[ CHUCKLES ]

12:26.392 --> 12:28.394
OKAY.

12:28.394 --> 12:30.731
WELL,
I WILL SEE YOU TONIGHT.

12:30.731 --> 12:33.734
YES.

12:44.477 --> 12:49.650
MM, KATHERYN,
YOUR TABLE IS LOVELY.

12:49.650 --> 12:50.684
THANK YOU.

12:50.684 --> 12:53.253
CELINE DOES SET
A NICE TABLE.

12:53.253 --> 12:55.355
SHE STILL WORKS HERE?
Enough.

12:55.355 --> 12:57.991
[ BOTH CHUCKLE ]

12:57.991 --> 13:01.001
Veronica: JEFFERY.
MOM.

13:01.001 --> 13:03.837
HELLO, MELISSA.
HI.

13:03.837 --> 13:05.539
HOW ARE YOU?
Melissa: I'M FINE.

13:05.539 --> 13:07.941
GOOD.
MELISSA, THIS IS MRS. CRYER.

13:07.941 --> 13:10.043
HELLO.
PLEASURE.

13:10.043 --> 13:11.978
HELLO, MRS. CRYER.

13:11.978 --> 13:13.880
WYATT.

13:13.880 --> 13:15.248
THIS IS MY SON,
WYATT.

13:15.248 --> 13:16.817
THIS IS MELISSA.

13:19.252 --> 13:20.420
HI.

13:20.420 --> 13:22.756
WHO'S THIS?

13:22.756 --> 13:26.359
THIS IS JEFFERY'S DATE.

13:28.094 --> 13:29.329
DATE?

13:34.100 --> 13:36.803
YES.
SHE WENT TO MY ALMA MATER.

13:36.803 --> 13:39.072
BUT I'M NOT BLAZING
THE TRAILS YOU DID.

13:39.072 --> 13:41.407
OH, YOU'RE DOING JUST FINE,
SWEETHEART.

13:41.407 --> 13:43.243
SHE'S QUITE BRIGHT,
YOU KNOW?

13:43.243 --> 13:45.946
Katheryn: AND QUITE BEAUTIFUL.
YES.

13:45.946 --> 13:48.815
HAVE A SEAT.

13:48.815 --> 13:50.884
HE'S SUCH A GENTLEMAN.
IS HE REALLY?

13:50.884 --> 13:52.786
HE REALLY IS.
I KNOW. I LOVE HIM.

13:52.786 --> 13:55.922
WELL, THAT DRESS IS
ABSOLUTELY BEAUTIFUL.

13:55.922 --> 13:57.357
THANK YOU SO MUCH.

13:57.357 --> 13:59.325
SO, HOW ARE YOU?

13:59.325 --> 14:01.502
I'M GOOD.

14:01.502 --> 14:03.704
OKAY.

14:03.704 --> 14:05.305
SO, IT ALL WORKED OUT?

14:05.305 --> 14:08.441
YEAH. YEAH, THANKS.
SURE.

14:11.377 --> 14:13.580
YOU LOOK LOVELY IN IT.
THANK YOU VERY MUCH.

14:13.580 --> 14:15.616
I LOVE YOUR BROOCH.
IT'S BEAUTIFUL.

14:15.616 --> 14:16.750
THANK YOU VERY MUCH.

14:16.750 --> 14:18.652
JIM BOUGHT THIS FOR ME,
ACTUALLY.

14:18.652 --> 14:19.953
REALLY?
YES, HE DID.

14:19.953 --> 14:21.722
YOU TAUGHT HIM WELL,
I'M SURE.

14:21.722 --> 14:23.724
WELL, TRYING TO TEACH AN OLD DOG
NEW TRICKS...

14:23.724 --> 14:24.991
[ BOTH CHUCKLE ]

14:32.666 --> 14:34.735
HEY.

14:34.735 --> 14:36.770
[ SIGHS ]

14:36.770 --> 14:38.605
I KNOW YOU'RE DOING THIS
FOR ME.

14:38.605 --> 14:41.307
LOOK AT ME.

14:43.443 --> 14:45.011
JEFFERY...

14:47.147 --> 14:49.750
THANK YOU.

14:49.750 --> 14:52.118
DON'T MENTION IT.

14:52.118 --> 14:54.354
I'M GONNA GO CHECK
ON DINNER.

14:54.354 --> 14:55.722
OKAY.

14:55.722 --> 15:00.066
JEFFERY, SON,
COME SIT WITH YOUR DATE.

15:08.141 --> 15:09.209
[ SIGHS ]

15:16.216 --> 15:17.383
HI, JIM.

15:17.383 --> 15:19.052
Jim: VERONICA.

15:19.052 --> 15:23.557
I SEE YOU MANAGED TO PULL OFF
A MIRACLE.

15:23.557 --> 15:25.659
YES, I DID.

15:25.659 --> 15:28.529
THANK YOU SO MUCH
FOR YOUR HELP.

15:28.529 --> 15:30.531
DON'T MENTION IT.

15:30.531 --> 15:32.065
WHERE'S KATHERYN?

15:32.065 --> 15:33.867
SHE'S IN THE KITCHEN.

15:33.867 --> 15:35.769
THANK YOU.

15:39.606 --> 15:41.341
HELLO.

15:41.341 --> 15:42.843
HELLO.

15:42.843 --> 15:44.645
DAVID,
THIS IS MELISSA.

15:44.645 --> 15:47.413
THIS IS JEFFERY'S DATE.

15:56.523 --> 15:58.725
UM...

15:58.725 --> 16:00.193
HOW ARE YOU?

16:00.193 --> 16:02.102
I'M GREAT.

16:02.102 --> 16:04.938
PLEASE, SIT DOWN.

16:09.543 --> 16:10.777
HONEY...
YES?

16:10.777 --> 16:13.246
David: DOESN'T KATHERYN SET
A LOVELY TABLE?

16:13.246 --> 16:15.015
YES, SHE DOES.

16:15.015 --> 16:17.984
Melissa:
HIS MOM INTRODUCED US.

16:17.984 --> 16:20.286
[ CHUCKLES ]
OH, OKAY, OKAY.

16:20.286 --> 16:22.956
WE WENT ON A DATE
TO HER FAVORITE RESTAURANT...

16:22.956 --> 16:26.359
WHAT WAS THAT?
DO YOU REMEMBER THE NAME?

16:26.359 --> 16:27.694
...A COUPLE DAYS AGO.

16:27.694 --> 16:29.863
WHAT IS JEFFERY DOING?

16:29.863 --> 16:32.365
WHAT DOES IT LOOK LIKE?

16:32.365 --> 16:37.003
IT LOOKS LIKE
HE IS VERY UNCOMFORTABLE.

16:37.003 --> 16:39.305
HE'LL GET COMFORTABLE.

16:39.305 --> 16:40.907
VERONICA ‐‐
I DON'T WANT TO HEAR IT.

16:43.877 --> 16:45.712
ENOUGH OF THIS.

16:45.712 --> 16:48.815
JEFFERY, I NEED TO SPEAK
WITH YOU FOR A MOMENT.

16:48.815 --> 16:51.051
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
ON THE LANAI, SON.

16:51.051 --> 16:53.319
I'M SORRY, MELISSA.
WE'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

16:53.319 --> 16:54.354
OKAY.

16:54.354 --> 16:55.922
I NEED TO SPEAK WITH MY SON
ALONE.

16:55.922 --> 16:57.490
THERE'S NOTHING YOU HAVE TO SAY
TO HIM

16:57.490 --> 16:58.925
THAT YOU CAN'T SAY
IN FRONT OF ME.

16:58.925 --> 17:02.669
I'M GOING TO SPEAK WITH MY SON
ALONE.

17:05.338 --> 17:07.774
FINE.

17:12.212 --> 17:13.980
GO ON, SON.

17:21.522 --> 17:23.524
SO...

17:36.402 --> 17:38.138
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

17:38.138 --> 17:40.507
[ SIGHS ]
I'M ON A DATE.

17:40.507 --> 17:42.042
I CAN SEE THAT.

17:42.042 --> 17:43.744
WHAT'S GOING ON,
JEFFERY?

17:43.744 --> 17:46.346
YOU ARE NOT INTERESTED IN DATING
THAT GIRL.

17:48.982 --> 17:50.250
MOM ‐‐

17:50.250 --> 17:53.520
NO, DON'T TALK TO ME
ABOUT YOUR MOTHER.

17:53.520 --> 17:55.756
TALK TO ME ABOUT
WHAT YOU WANT.

17:55.756 --> 17:59.660
I MEAN,
SHE'S A CUTE GIRL.

17:59.660 --> 18:00.661
JEFFERY.

18:00.661 --> 18:02.736
DAD, I WILL, JUST LET ME ‐‐
NO, NO.

18:02.736 --> 18:04.838
YOU'LL JUST RUIN
THAT GIRL'S LIFE,

18:04.838 --> 18:07.140
AND I AM NOT ABOUT
TO LET THAT HAPPEN.

18:07.140 --> 18:08.775
YOU ARE GAY.

18:08.775 --> 18:11.612
YOU ARE NOT INTERESTED
IN DATING A WOMAN.

18:11.612 --> 18:14.380
MOM WANTS ME TO.

18:14.380 --> 18:18.051
ARE YOU THAT AFRAID
OF YOUR MOTHER?

18:18.051 --> 18:20.954
NO, I‐I JUST ‐‐
I CAN'T ‐‐

18:20.954 --> 18:23.189
YES, YES. YOU ARE.

18:23.189 --> 18:25.258
YOU WAIT RIGHT HERE.

18:27.728 --> 18:31.397
David: VERONICA!
VERONICA!

18:31.397 --> 18:33.667
[ SIGHS ]

18:33.667 --> 18:36.169
Veronica: WELL, SEE,
I TOLD YOU HE WOULD NEED ME.

18:38.371 --> 18:41.675
JEFFERY IS NOT INTERESTED
IN DATING THAT GIRL.

18:41.675 --> 18:43.443
I DON'T SEE WHY NOT.

18:43.443 --> 18:44.578
SHE'S CUTE.

18:44.578 --> 18:47.447
SHE LOOKS A LITTLE LIKE ME,
DON'T YOU THINK?

18:47.447 --> 18:49.449
HE IS GAY.

18:49.449 --> 18:51.752
VERONICA ‐‐

18:51.752 --> 18:53.654
JEFFERY,
YOU DON'T HAVE TO DO THIS.

18:53.654 --> 18:55.922
OH, YES, HE DOES.

18:58.158 --> 19:01.502
HE'S AFRAID THAT HIS MOTHER
WILL TURN HIM IN.

19:01.502 --> 19:03.203
AND DO YOU THINK
I WON'T?

19:03.203 --> 19:05.238
NO, YOU WON'T.

19:05.238 --> 19:07.941
NOW, JUST TELL ME
WHERE HIS CAR IS.

19:07.941 --> 19:10.611
TRY ME.

19:10.611 --> 19:13.246
PLEASE.

19:13.246 --> 19:15.782
I DON'T KNOW YOU.

19:15.782 --> 19:19.019
I DON'T KNOW YOU
AT ALL.

19:19.019 --> 19:21.588
IT'S FINE. IT'S ‐‐ IT'S FINE.
IT'S JUST A DATE.

19:21.588 --> 19:23.023
YOU'RE NOT HAPPY.

19:23.023 --> 19:24.691
I CAN BE.
I CAN BE.

19:24.691 --> 19:26.126
NOT LIVING LIKE THIS
YOU CAN'T.

19:26.126 --> 19:27.894
[ SIGHS ] CAN WE ‐‐

19:27.894 --> 19:30.196
PLEASE, CAN WE JUST GO IN
AND HAVE A GOOD TIME?

19:30.196 --> 19:32.498
PLEASE?
SON ‐‐

19:32.498 --> 19:34.234
DAD,
DON'T WORRY ABOUT ME.

19:34.234 --> 19:39.005
SON, LISTEN TO ME.

19:39.005 --> 19:41.842
YOU CAN'T LIVE YOUR LIFE
FALLING ON YOUR SWORD

19:41.842 --> 19:43.309
TO PROTECT EVERYONE ELSE.

19:46.179 --> 19:50.784
IN THE LONG RUN...

19:50.784 --> 19:54.521
IT WILL SUFFOCATE YOU
AND MAKE YOU MISERABLE

19:54.521 --> 19:57.658
BECAUSE OF
THE CONSTANT SACRIFICE.

20:01.568 --> 20:07.007
AND THAT...WOULD BE
A REFERENCE TO ME?

20:07.007 --> 20:10.310
PLEASE DON'T FIGHT
ABOUT THIS.

20:54.187 --> 20:56.690
WHAT IS WRONG
WITH YOU?

20:56.690 --> 20:59.125
NOTHING.
I'M WAITING FOR SOMEONE.

20:59.125 --> 21:01.001
WHO?
[ DOORBELL RINGS ]

21:01.001 --> 21:03.003
NO ONE NOW.

21:11.177 --> 21:14.314
HEY.

21:14.314 --> 21:16.049
I'M SORRY.
HOW ARE YOU?

21:16.049 --> 21:18.619
I'M OKAY.

21:18.619 --> 21:20.754
COME ON IN.

21:25.892 --> 21:30.263
MOM, DAD,
THIS IS QUINCY.

21:30.263 --> 21:32.332
QUINCY.

21:32.332 --> 21:34.568
MM, YOU HAVE A NAME.

21:34.568 --> 21:36.503
YEAH, I DO.

21:36.503 --> 21:37.804
DO YOU HAVE A NAME?

21:40.541 --> 21:44.344
YES.
I'M KATHERYN CRYER.

21:44.344 --> 21:46.312
I'M AMANDA'S MOTHER.

21:46.312 --> 21:49.182
THIS IS HER FATHER,
JIM.

21:49.182 --> 21:51.918
DAVID AND VERONICA,
MY SON, WYATT.

21:51.918 --> 21:53.754
THIS IS
JEFFERY AND MELISSA.

21:53.754 --> 21:58.191
OH, YOU THAT...JUDGE.

21:58.191 --> 22:02.168
YES, I'M THAT...JUDGE.

22:02.168 --> 22:05.071
I'M JUDGE JIM CRYER.

22:05.071 --> 22:08.141
THIS IS
JUDGE DAVID HARRINGTON.

22:08.141 --> 22:09.142
WHAT UP, NIG‐‐

22:09.142 --> 22:11.311
I DON'T KNOW
WHERE YOU'RE FROM, SON,

22:11.311 --> 22:13.313
BUT THAT KIND OF LANGUAGE

22:13.313 --> 22:15.415
WILL SEND YOU BACK THERE
VERY QUICKLY.

22:15.415 --> 22:20.186
YOU WILL NOT USE THAT LANGUAGE
IN THIS HOUSE...BOY.

22:21.788 --> 22:28.261
SO, AMANDA, HOW LONG
HAVE YOU KNOWN...QUINCY?

22:28.261 --> 22:30.731
A COUPLE OF DAYS.

22:30.731 --> 22:32.733
HE JUST GOT OUT OF JAIL.

22:32.733 --> 22:34.100
IS THAT RIGHT?

22:34.100 --> 22:37.971
YEAH.
HE WAS IN JAIL FOR MURDER.

22:37.971 --> 22:41.608
AND WHERE DID YOU MEET?

22:41.608 --> 22:43.610
HE'S A FRIEND
OF CANDACE'S.

22:43.610 --> 22:45.145
HE WAS LOOKING FOR HER.

22:45.145 --> 22:47.480
AND NOW YOU'RE DATING HIM.

22:47.480 --> 22:49.750
HOPE TO MARRY.

22:49.750 --> 22:53.053
NOT OFFICIALLY,
BUT ARE WE DATING?

22:53.053 --> 22:55.255
WHATEVER
YOUR SWEET ASS WANT.

22:55.255 --> 22:56.623
YEAH, WE'RE DATING.

22:56.623 --> 22:58.458
AMANDA ‐‐
WHAT, MO?!

22:58.458 --> 23:00.126
IF HE CAN DATE SOMEONE
THAT'S ALL WRONG FOR HIM,

23:00.126 --> 23:03.336
THEN I CAN CERTAINLY DATE
SOMEONE THAT'S ALL WRONG FOR ME.

23:06.907 --> 23:09.510
LISTEN, QUENTIN ‐‐
WHAT IS YOUR NAME?

23:09.510 --> 23:11.945
QUINCY, BITCH.

23:11.945 --> 23:14.548
WELL, MR. QUINCY BITCH,

23:14.548 --> 23:16.850
WOULD YOU MIND HAVING
A LITTLE CONVERSATION WITH ME

23:16.850 --> 23:18.952
IN MY OFFICE,
IN PRIVATE?

23:18.952 --> 23:21.487
OH, YEAH.

23:24.090 --> 23:25.626
SHOULD I ACCOMPANY YOU,
JIM?

23:25.626 --> 23:28.529
NO. I‐I GOT THIS.

23:32.298 --> 23:35.235
SHALL WE SIT?

23:35.235 --> 23:37.704
[ SIGHS ]

23:41.775 --> 23:44.344
[ SIGHS ]
WELL, NOW...

23:57.157 --> 23:59.025
I DON'T KNOW WHO THE HELL
YOU THINK YOU ARE

23:59.025 --> 24:01.401
OR WHAT THE HELL YOU THINK
YOU'RE DOING WITH MY DAUGHTER,

24:01.401 --> 24:03.704
BUT I'M GONNA GIVE YOU
ONE LAST CHANCE

24:03.704 --> 24:06.106
TO LEAVE HER ALONE AND
GET THE HELL OUT OF MY HOUSE.

24:06.106 --> 24:07.674
YOU HITTING MY CHICK?

24:07.674 --> 24:10.911
WHAT?
I NEVER HIT ANYBODY.

24:10.911 --> 24:14.480
BANGING, SCREWING,
SEX, FU‐‐

24:14.480 --> 24:15.782
OH, COME ON! HEY!

24:15.782 --> 24:18.318
I UNDERSTAND.
CANDACE PUT YOU UP TO THIS.

24:18.318 --> 24:21.254
SHE'S GOT YOU
RIGHT WHERE SHE'S GOT ME.

24:21.254 --> 24:23.289
WHERE IS SHE?

24:23.289 --> 24:25.025
WHERE IS WHO?

24:25.025 --> 24:27.427
CANDACE.

24:27.427 --> 24:31.698
LITTLE BIRDIE TOLD ME

24:31.698 --> 24:33.900
SHE BEEN MESSING AROUND
WITH YOU,

24:33.900 --> 24:35.936
AND NOW CAN'T NOBODY
FIND HER.

24:35.936 --> 24:38.839
I'M GONNA ASK YOU
ONE LAST TIME.

24:38.839 --> 24:40.040
WHERE IS SHE?

24:40.040 --> 24:44.578
I DON'T KNOW,
AND I DON'T CARE.

24:44.578 --> 24:46.847
NOW, YOU GET THE HELL OUT
OF MY ‐‐

24:46.847 --> 24:49.750
[ BOTH GRUNTING ]

24:49.750 --> 24:51.652
WHERE IS SHE?!
WHERE IS SHE?!

24:51.652 --> 24:54.521
[ MUFFLED GRUNTING ]

24:56.056 --> 24:58.725
HEY! HEY!
WHERE IS CANDACE?

24:58.725 --> 25:00.827
[ Strained ]
I DON'T KNOW WHERE SHE IS!

25:00.827 --> 25:02.969
WHERE IS SHE?
I DON'T KNOW.

25:02.969 --> 25:05.138
WHERE IS SHE?
I DON'T KNOW!

25:05.138 --> 25:06.807
WHERE IS SHE?!

25:09.342 --> 25:11.344
WHERE IS SHE?!
Jim: I DON'T KNOW!

25:11.344 --> 25:13.647
GET HIM OUT OF HERE!

25:15.048 --> 25:16.883
GET HIM OUT OF HERE!
GET OFF ME!

25:24.691 --> 25:26.392
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

25:26.392 --> 25:27.628
I GOT TO GO.

25:27.628 --> 25:29.830
GET ME UP.
GET ME UP.

25:29.830 --> 25:31.898
YOU OKAY?

25:33.700 --> 25:35.536
GET OFF OF ME!

25:35.536 --> 25:36.703
AMANDA!

25:36.703 --> 25:38.304
Katheryn:
WHAT THE HELL IS GOING ON, JIM?

25:38.304 --> 25:40.206
AMANDA!

25:40.206 --> 25:41.642
SHE LEFT,
GONE OUT THE DOOR.

25:41.642 --> 25:44.044
SHUT UP, KATHERYN!
SHUT UP!

25:44.044 --> 25:45.145
AMANDA!

25:45.145 --> 25:47.147
DAD, WHAT DID YOU DO?!

25:47.147 --> 25:48.682
GET IN THE HOUSE RIGHT NOW,
SWEETHEART.

25:48.682 --> 25:50.684
NO! QUINCY!

25:50.684 --> 25:52.485
I GOT TO GO.
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

25:52.485 --> 25:54.788
AMANDA, GET BACK IN THE HOUSE.
DAD, WHAT DID YOU DO?

25:54.788 --> 25:56.690
NO!
BACK IN THE HOUSE, NOW.

25:56.690 --> 25:58.792
NO.
QUINCY, W‐WHAT HAPPENED?

25:58.792 --> 26:00.734
ASKED YOUR DADDY
WHY HE BEEN SCREWING MY GIRL.

26:00.734 --> 26:02.335
WHAT?

26:02.335 --> 26:03.303
CANDACE.

26:03.303 --> 26:05.572
YOUR DADDY'S BEEN SCREWING
CANDACE.

26:05.572 --> 26:07.808
WHAT?

26:07.808 --> 26:10.176
WHAT IS
HE TALKING ABOUT?

26:12.178 --> 26:13.914
I WANT EVERYBODY
TO GET INSIDE NOW.

26:13.914 --> 26:16.783
[ ENGINE TURNS OVER ]
GO ON! GET INSIDE!

26:19.452 --> 26:20.987
HE'S DELUSIONAL.

26:20.987 --> 26:22.789
IS HE?
YES.

26:22.789 --> 26:24.825
OH, LIKE I AM?
NO.

26:24.825 --> 26:27.260
AMANDA, COME IN THE HOUSE.
SO, WYATT WAS RIGHT.

26:27.260 --> 26:29.996
WHAT DOES THAT
EVEN MEAN?

26:29.996 --> 26:31.832
HE SAID
WHEN HE FIRST SAW CANDACE,

26:31.832 --> 26:33.867
THAT YOU WERE MESSING AROUND
WITH HER.

26:33.867 --> 26:36.670
AND THEN WHEN I CAME HOME THAT
DAY, YOU WERE AT MY APARTMENT.

26:36.670 --> 26:38.639
I THOUGHT
IT WAS STRANGE.

26:38.639 --> 26:40.807
AND THEN SOMETIMES,
SHE WOULD COME IN

26:40.807 --> 26:44.210
AFTER STUDYING WITH YOU,
AND I WOULD SMELL YOUR COLOGNE.

26:44.210 --> 26:47.848
YOU HAVE BEEN.

26:47.848 --> 26:49.249
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]

26:49.249 --> 26:51.952
AMANDA...

26:51.952 --> 26:53.887
DON'T LIE TO ME, DAD!

26:58.158 --> 26:59.993
CAN YOU PLEASE GO INSIDE

26:59.993 --> 27:03.203
AND LEAVE ME HERE
TO TALK WITH MY DAUGHTER?

27:04.605 --> 27:07.508
ANSWER HER, JIM.

27:09.743 --> 27:11.244
[ SNIFFLES ]

27:13.213 --> 27:17.483
YOUR BOYFRIEND, QUINCY...

27:21.321 --> 27:22.889
...IS LYING.

27:22.889 --> 27:24.758
YEAH, WHY WOULD HE?

27:24.758 --> 27:26.660
BECAUSE HE'S A CONVICT.

27:26.660 --> 27:29.262
AMANDA.

27:34.367 --> 27:35.569
I WANT YOU TO FIND OUT

27:35.569 --> 27:37.671
EVERYTHING YOU CAN
ABOUT THAT BASTARD.

27:37.671 --> 27:39.840
I'M ON IT.

27:39.840 --> 27:41.742
AND IF HE WAS IN PRISON
FOR MURDER,

27:41.742 --> 27:43.544
HOW THE HELL
DID HE GET OUT?!

28:05.572 --> 28:09.009
[ PIANO PLAYS ]

28:20.120 --> 28:21.988
[ CHUCKLES ]

28:21.988 --> 28:24.424
NO. NO, NO, NO.
KEEP GOING.

28:24.424 --> 28:27.093
NO,
I THINK I'LL STOP HERE.

28:27.093 --> 28:30.263
WELL, THEN, I'M NOT RESPONSIBLE
FOR WHAT I SAY.

28:30.263 --> 28:32.365
I'M DRINKING.

28:32.365 --> 28:35.201
SO BE IT.

28:35.201 --> 28:39.239
I'M SORRY
FOR VERONICA'S BEHAVIOR.

28:42.509 --> 28:44.911
I COULD TALK TO HER.

28:44.911 --> 28:46.947
REALLY?

28:46.947 --> 28:48.615
[ CHUCKLES ] YES.

28:48.615 --> 28:49.816
AND SAY WHAT?

28:49.816 --> 28:53.119
YOU SMILE LIKE I'M POWERLESS,
DAVID.

28:53.119 --> 28:56.823
NO, NO.
I KNOW YOU HAVE POWER.

28:56.823 --> 28:59.459
THEN WHY SO SMUG?

28:59.459 --> 29:04.605
MY WIFE IS
A WONDERFULLY STRONG,

29:04.605 --> 29:08.642
HARDHEADED,
AND SOMETIMES STUBBORN WOMAN.

29:08.642 --> 29:10.944
SHE'S COMING AROUND.

29:16.049 --> 29:17.984
ARE YOU HAPPY WITH HER?

29:20.253 --> 29:22.523
YEAH.

29:22.523 --> 29:25.992
WELL,
THAT'S PRETTY GOOD.

29:25.992 --> 29:28.294
WHAT?

29:28.294 --> 29:30.531
MM,
THE LIE YOU JUST TOLD.

29:30.531 --> 29:33.700
I LOVE MY WIFE.

29:33.700 --> 29:35.702
[ CHUCKLES ]
NO, I KNOW.

29:35.702 --> 29:38.004
BUT THAT'S NOT THE ANSWER
TO THE QUESTION.

29:41.174 --> 29:43.409
I AM HAPPY.

29:46.980 --> 29:48.682
YOU WANT A DRINK?

29:51.084 --> 29:55.488
CAN I GET A SCOTCH NEAT,
DOUBLE?

29:55.488 --> 29:58.358
DOUBLE.

29:58.358 --> 30:03.504
GUESS YOU NEED THAT DRINK,
HUH, MR. HAPPY.

30:03.504 --> 30:05.338
[ CHUCKLES ]

30:05.338 --> 30:09.576
BY THE WAY, I KNOW
THE, UH, "I'M HAPPY" IS A LIE.

30:09.576 --> 30:12.078
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

30:12.078 --> 30:14.848
BODY LANGUAGE, DAVID.

30:14.848 --> 30:17.283
YOUR EYES MOVE ONE WAY
WHEN YOU'RE TELLING A LIE

30:17.283 --> 30:19.452
AND ANOTHER WHEN YOU'RE TELLING
THE TRUTH.

30:19.452 --> 30:21.922
I CAN TELL BY THE WAY THE WORDS
ARE FORMED

30:21.922 --> 30:23.256
IF YOU'RE LYING OR NOT.

30:23.256 --> 30:27.761
SO, YOU'RE AN EXPERT
IN BODY LANGUAGE?

30:27.761 --> 30:31.197
WELL, IT IS MY JOB.

30:31.197 --> 30:33.466
OKAY.

30:38.171 --> 30:40.440
SO, CAN I ASK YOU
A FEW QUESTIONS?

30:40.440 --> 30:43.276
OH, I SEE.

30:43.276 --> 30:46.279
YOU WANT TO ‐‐
YOU WANT TO PLAY WORD GAMES.

30:46.279 --> 30:49.249
[ CHUCKLES ]
NO. NO GAMES.

30:49.249 --> 30:51.818
I NEED TO TEACH YOU
TO BE UNREADABLE.

30:53.654 --> 30:56.189
OH. OKAY.

30:56.189 --> 30:59.192
PROCEED.

30:59.192 --> 31:01.301
[ SIGHS ]

31:01.301 --> 31:04.905
WHY IS YOUR SON
SO SAD?

31:09.109 --> 31:11.545
JEFFERY'S GOING THROUGH
A LOT.

31:11.545 --> 31:14.447
SUCH AS?

31:14.447 --> 31:17.818
SOMETHING I DON'T CARE
TO DISCUSS WITH YOU.

31:17.818 --> 31:19.920
[ CHUCKLES LIGHTLY ]

31:19.920 --> 31:23.256
I LOVE HOW PROTECTIVE
YOU ARE OF HIM.

31:23.256 --> 31:25.592
YES, VERY MUCH.

31:25.592 --> 31:28.128
OKAY.

31:28.128 --> 31:31.297
WHY IS YOUR WIFE SUCH A BITCH
SOMETIMES?

31:31.297 --> 31:34.067
MY WIFE IS NOT A BITCH.

31:34.067 --> 31:35.769
YOU SAY THAT AGAIN,
IT'S GOOD NIGHT.

31:35.769 --> 31:38.471
MM. YOU'RE PROTECTIVE
OF HER, TOO.

31:38.471 --> 31:40.641
VERY MUCH.

31:40.641 --> 31:42.676
SHE'S A LUCKY FOOL.

31:42.676 --> 31:46.246
WELL, MAYBE I AM.

31:48.949 --> 31:51.518
OKAY.
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

31:51.518 --> 31:53.754
ANOTHER QUESTION.

31:56.723 --> 31:57.958
ALL RIGHT.

32:00.661 --> 32:03.203
ARE YOU JEALOUS OF JIM?

32:03.203 --> 32:04.705
JEALOUS?

32:04.705 --> 32:06.439
YEAH.

32:06.439 --> 32:09.242
YOU KNOW,
ALL‐AMERICAN WHITE MAN,

32:09.242 --> 32:12.212
AND YOU HAVE TO BE
IN HIS SHADOW.

32:12.212 --> 32:15.115
AND EVEN THOUGH THERE'S
AN AFRICAN‐AMERICAN PRESIDENT,

32:15.115 --> 32:17.651
THIS STATE ISN'T READY FOR
AN AFRICAN‐AMERICAN GOVERNOR.

32:20.954 --> 32:22.523
ARE YOU JEALOUS?

32:22.523 --> 32:25.258
NOT AT ALL.

32:26.793 --> 32:28.929
I'M A MAN
WHO IS COMFORTABLE

32:28.929 --> 32:32.065
IN MY OWN ACCOMPLISHMENTS
AND MY OWN SKIN.

32:32.065 --> 32:35.902
THAT WAS TRUTH.

32:35.902 --> 32:39.205
THAT'S GOOD.

32:39.205 --> 32:42.075
YES, YOU ARE.

32:42.075 --> 32:44.678
AND WHAT BEAUTIFUL SKIN
IT IS.

32:47.748 --> 32:51.484
ARE YOU FINISHED
WITH YOUR QUESTIONS?

32:51.484 --> 32:54.187
IT'S BEEN A LONG DAY,
AND I'M TIRED.

32:54.187 --> 32:56.422
SURE.

32:56.422 --> 32:59.125
WELL, MAYBE ONE MORE,
THOUGH.

33:01.134 --> 33:03.136
MM.
[ LAUGHS ]

33:03.136 --> 33:05.772
ALL RIGHT. JUST ONE.

